	     Craig S.  Morford
	     
	  



health products executive, 
prosecutor



		Craig S. Morford, American health products executive, former prosecutor. Named Outstanding Assistant United States Attorney, National Association Former United States Attorneys, 2005; recipient Director award for Superior Performance, United States Department Justice, 1996, 2000,  Attorney General Disting Service award, 2003, 2005. Fellow: American College Trial Lawyers.
		
       		



Background




Morford, Craig S. was born on February 10, 1959 in Schenectady, New York, United States.
					
					



Education


	 		
			

			Bachelor in Economic, Hope College, 1981. Juris Doctor, Valparaiso University School Law, 1984.
			
       			












Career


	 		
			Trial attorney Office Chief Counsel Internal Revenue Service, 1984—1987. Special trial attorney Cleveland Organized Crime Taskforce United States Department Justice, 1986—1989, assistant United States attorney (northern district) OH, 1989—2002, interim United States attorney (eastern district) Michigan, 2004—2005, special attorney to United States attorney general heading investigation into first major United States post September 11th trial, 2004, 1st. United States attorney (northern district) Ohio, 2005—2006, interim United States attorney (middle district) Tennessee, 2006—2007, acting deputy attorney general, 2007—2008.Chief compliance officer Cardinal Health, Inc., Dublin, since 2008, chief legal officer, since 2009.
			
       			












Membership


			Fellow: American College Trial Lawyers.
			
    			







Connections


			Married; 4 children.
			
    			








